The paper discusses the application of a combination rule in information fusion for two different applications: sonar imagery and radar targets classification. These applications involve image processing and classification, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE). The use of information fusion also suggests a potential connection to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
